article.headline: Holy Cross 68, Bucknell 56
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Andrew Keister had 18 points and 10 rebounds and Pat Doherty also scored 18 points on 13-of-14 free-throw shooting to lead Holy Cross to a 68-56 victory over Bucknell on Saturday. Alex Vander Baan chipped in 11 points for Holy Cross (8-10, 3-0 Patriot League). Patrick Behan scored 12 points and Jason Vegotsky and G.W. Boon each had 11 for Bucknell (3-14, 0-3). Bucknell trailed 30-15 at halftime but went on a 15-7 run to narrow the gap to 48-45 with 5:24 remaining on a 3-pointer by Boon. But a 3-pointer and five free-throws by Vander Baan helped Holy Cross push the margin back to 60-49 with 1:25 remaining.
